    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9681" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χραισμέω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χρήσιμος</span>), aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔχραισμε, χραῖσμε</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χραίσμῃ</span>(<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">σι</span>), <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-ωσι</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-εῖν</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χραισμήσω</span>,
          inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-σέμεν</span>, aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χραίσμησε</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">-ῆσαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">be useful</span> to one in something
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί τι</span>), <i><span class="en">Il. 7.144</span></i>; hence <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">avail, help, ward off</span>
          something, abs., and w. acc. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τὶ</span>),
            <i><span class="en">Il. 1.566</span></i>, 589. Always with
          negative.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
